OpenExcimer Precompliance Notes

1)The high voltage ballast (driver) and 24V ac/dc offline converter combination were placed in a linear arrangement. 
2)The ballst and ad/dc supply were connected with a short cable. 
3)No other filtering, mitigation or other steps were taken (as would be common in a commercial product).
4)The intent of this test is to show that the OpenExcimer passes the more stringest FCC Part 15 Subpart B Class B standards - as is without modification.
5)Final integration into a final product and subsequent certification of the same are outside the scope of the Open Excimer project.
6)It should be noted that the conducted mode compliance is highly sensitive to physical placement and the primary EMI agressors are fields originating from the high voltage transformer and switching section - care should be taken to seperate (by distance) and shield other parts of your luminiare design from this - in particular - the design can experience unintended interference if the ac/dc converter and high voltage ballast (driver) are placed side by side or in a parallel configuration which allows more of the fields to couple. 